<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufelisandria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>felisandria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/24/01 11:51:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: the blame game</span><hr size=1> Oh, absolutely Misy.<br>
<br>
I had meant to add that destructive habits aren't exactly something that you'd want to try with your spouse (smoking, drinking, drugs, etc) to forward your relationship... but if it's a harmless activity (going to watch a movie you wouldn't usually watch, for example) it might give you some insight into your spouse.  Or, even pick an activity that you haven't tried yet.<br>
<br>
I think that's one important thing, to be willing to try things with your spouse and be willing to um... look foolish or act like a kid.  I can remember a lot of things (trying to stand up on rollerblades, getting severe bottom-bruises trying to snowboard, winding up with a hopelessly tangled fly-fishing line) that made me feel silly but I've never felt like I have to be perfect or poised around Mya, and that helps a lot.  There's a lot of bonding that goes on when you do things together, even when they go wrong.  Maybe especially when they go wrong... some of my fondest memories involve getting an old beaten up Scout II nearly inextricably stuck in the middle of nowhere.  Shared experiences are what keep people on the same page.  <br>
<br>
That doesn't mean that spouses have to have all the same hobbies, but at least being open to each others hobbies, or if you already know you hate the other person's hobbies trying out a new one, will help so much more than writing a celebrity about how awful your spouse is for doing XXX (where doing XXX isn't destructive behavior like alcoholism or abuse).  I bet that husband would get soooo much farther by just telling his wife that he will spend some time playing with her and then they can go do something he wants to do.<br>
<br>
-fel <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.showMessage?topicID=6576.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.showMessage?topicID=6578.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=6560.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.threadControl?topicID=6560.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6560.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumgeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6560.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub4.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="eqasylumgeneral">General<option value="eqasylumfrm25">Raid Discussions<option value="eqasylumthetavernincharacterdiscussion">The Tavern <option value="eqasylumthemerchantsunionbuyselltradeorannounceyourservicesforhire">The Merchant's Union<option value="eqasylumbiographiessharesomeinfoaboutyourself">Biographies <option value="eqasylumplayerrunquestsorganizeandfindactorsfordynamicquests">Player Run Quests <option value="eqasylumlookingforgroupannounceplanorjoinraidsandgroups">Looking for grou